{"can_edit": true, "from": {"name": "Micha\u00ebl Caron Couturier", "id": "1646843124"}, "revision": "10152649229475019", "updated_time": "2013-02-25T22:25:12+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2013-02-25T22:10:14+0000", "message": "<p><strong>Recommanded distro to start :</strong></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><strong>Linux Mint 13 Xfce</strong></p>\n<p>http://www.linuxmint.com/release.php?id=18</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><strong>32 bits or 64 bits :</strong></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Under 4Gb of ram 32 bits is better, at 4Gb or better, use 64 bits or at least a 32 bits PAE kernel that will allow to use the ram over 3,5Gb</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><strong>Easy suggestion to make it even more lightweight and fast :</strong></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>sudo apt-get install openbox obconf</p>\n<p>Then follow this tutorial :</p>\n<p>http://openbox.org/wiki/Help:XFCE/Openbox</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><strong>Troubleshooting advice :</strong></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Use google and seek for keywords related to your problem and the word Ubuntu, Ubuntu being the base distro of Mint, this will give out more results to help you ...</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Use Google translate to seek for the amazing french documention of Ubuntu that may be fairly decent for beginners also ...</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>http://doc.ubuntu-fr.org/</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><em><strong>*Xfce is the base of most of the LTS of Ubuntu and Linux Mint, is stable, well featured and lightweight enough for any use*</strong></em></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><em><strong>*LTS releases have 3 years of desktop support, including 2 years for new hardware  support, regular releases only get 18 months of support without added  hardware support*</strong></em></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><em><strong>*Mint is taken for codecs, flash, java usable from the live dvd/usb so it&#039;s pretty useful ...*</strong></em></p>", "subject": "Recommandations for beginners", "id": "10152649184365019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/yi/r/-64q65AWgXb.png"}